{
  "stem": "3659.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Because we shipped some of the things because we couldn't take money with us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I mean, at least so we had a few belongings that we-- we-- we bought our own belongings to ship them out and to send them the-- to America.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So that is what-- and there were inspectors that came to the house that watched every piece that went out and took inventory and put the amount down what-- what that piece would cost if you would buy it today.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I remember my mother had a Bosendorfer piano, and she loved it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Of course, we all played, you know, music.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So we shipped the Bosendorfer out, and we had to buy our own Bosendorfer.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So it was very strange during that period of time because money was really the-- was really the only surviving thing that you had.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And once we knew that we were all set with our affidavits and the visas for us, we were able to smuggle our father out on a banana boat to the British West Indies, which we did in December.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And we bought him passage on a banana boat.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We had no idea how he was going to survive there or whatever.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But once we knew he was on the high seas, we were able to go to the American Consulate and say, the visas, split them, he will have to take care of himself, and we are taking care of ourselves.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we were able to-- by that time we had nothing left in the house anymore, because the few belongings we had, you know, we shipped to the United States.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The people were still living in our house.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We-- whatever we could, get food, you know, we-- we did.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We-- we bought it and fed everybody.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
